<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-08-02T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-08-02T09:00:00-05:00" n="880" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d880">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Palestine/8–249:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">
                                    <persName type="from">Mr. Paul A. Porter</persName> to the
                                        <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lausanne</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-02T15:00:00+01:00">August
                                        2, 1949—3 p. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <gloss target="#t_Palun1">Palun</gloss> 260. Reference <gloss target="#t_Palun1">Palun</gloss> 253.<note n="1" xml:id="d880fn1">Dated July 28, from Lausanne, <ref target="#pg_1266">p. 1266</ref>.</note> In meeting with
                                    <gloss target="#t_PCC1">PCC</gloss> August 2 Arab delegates
                                accepted conditions set by Israelis as basis for discussion refugee
                                problem. Delegates demonstrated cooperative attitude.</p>
                            <p>
                                <gloss target="#t_PCC1">PCC</gloss> immediately proceeding meet
                                Shiloah obtain for transmission Arab delegations terms Israeli
                                proposal re refugees.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Porter</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>